GRAMMAR

Word Formation

Words are often formed through compounding, as well as, less often through derivation by affixes.

Word Order

The standard word order is SOV

Nouns

Nouns can be inflected for 2 numbers, Dual and Plural

To Dualize, add the prefix of Teja- or if the word starts with a Vowel Tej-
To Pluralize, add a prefix of Keta- or if the word starts with a Vowel Ket-

Possesives are formed using the possive particle nge, ie. Maro nge te (Lit, Cat POSS me), trans. My Cat

